# Trivy ignore list — controlled via PR review.
#
# Each entry MUST include:
#   - CVE id
#   - one-line reason for ignoring (e.g. "false positive: package not used at runtime",
#     "fix pending upstream, mitigated by NetworkPolicy", "vulnerable code path
#     unreachable")
#   - link to the PR that added it
#
# Example:
# CVE-2024-XXXXX  # not exploitable: only loaded in test env (#42)

# ---- Phase 2.5 initial baseline (PR #3) ----
# All three are unreachable at runtime; follow-up issue: clean builder leftovers + bump distroless.

# libpython3.11-minimal DoS via http.client — we don't use http.client (httpx instead).
# Fixed in 3.11.2-6+deb12u7; will pick up via next distroless `:nonroot` rebuild.
CVE-2025-13836

# jaraco.context — pulled in by setuptools as a transitive build-time dep; not invoked at runtime.
CVE-2026-23949

# wheel — pip/uv build-time dep; runtime never installs packages.
CVE-2026-24049

# ---- Phase 11 follow-up ----
# krb5 (libgssapi-krb5-2 / libk5crypto3 / libkrb5-3 / libkrb5support0) DoS via
# integer overflow. Comes from the distroless debian-12 base, NOT our deps.
# Unreachable: this service uses no Kerberos/GSSAPI (Postgres = password auth,
# providers = HTTPS). distroless has no apt to patch in place; fixed upstream in
# 1.20.1-2+deb12u5 — will clear via the next distroless `:nonroot` rebuild.
CVE-2026-40356

# ---- 2026-06-01: frontend image ----
# libxml2 (2.13.9-r0) DoS via crafted XML in nginx-unprivileged:1.27-alpine base.
# Unreachable: the frontend nginx serves static SPA + reverse-proxies HTTP only,
# never parses XML. libxml2 is a transitive Alpine base dep, not invoked at
# runtime. apk upgrade --no-cache (already in Dockerfile.frontend) will pick up
# the fix automatically once Alpine publishes 2.13.9-r1.
CVE-2026-6732

# ---- 2026-06-10: backend distroless base (PR #76) ----
# libssl3 (openssl 3.0.x) — crafted PKCS#7 / S-MIME signed message parsing flaw.
# Unreachable: this service uses libssl only as a TLS *client* (HTTPS to trusted
# providers — Azure/OpenAI/Anthropic — and Postgres); it never parses
# attacker-controlled PKCS#7 or S/MIME signed content, so the vulnerable path is
# not exercised. Comes from the distroless debian-12 base, NOT our deps; no apt
# to patch in place. Fixed upstream in 3.0.20-1~deb12u2 — clears via the next
# distroless `:nonroot` rebuild.
CVE-2026-45447

# ---- 2026-06-27: starlette (PR #92) ----
# starlette 0.50.0 is PINNED by FastAPI 0.124.x (starlette<0.51); both CVEs are
# only fixed in starlette 1.x, which needs a FastAPI major bump — tracked as a
# dedicated supply-chain task (階段 35), NOT smuggled into a frontend PR.
#
# CVE-2026-48818 — SSRF + NTLM credential theft via UNC paths. UNC (\\server\share)
# is a Windows SMB concept; this service runs on Linux distroless and never resolves
# attacker-controlled UNC/file paths (the backend serves no user-pathed static files
# — the SPA is served by the separate frontend nginx). Not exploitable here.
CVE-2026-48818

# CVE-2026-54283 — starlette ASGI framework advisory, fixed in 1.3.1 (same 1.x
# major-bump blocker as above). Mitigated by being behind the frontend nginx +
# NetworkPolicy; will clear when the starlette/FastAPI bump (階段 35) lands.
CVE-2026-54283

# ---- 2026-06-27: frontend image (PR #92) ----
# libexpat (2.7.5-r0) DoS via crafted XML in nginx-unprivileged:1.27-alpine base.
# Unreachable: the frontend nginx serves a static SPA + reverse-proxies HTTP only,
# never parses XML; libexpat is a transitive Alpine base dep, not invoked at runtime
# (same class as the libxml2 entry above). apk upgrade --no-cache (already in
# Dockerfile.frontend) picks up the fix once Alpine publishes 2.8.1-r0.
CVE-2026-45186
